^-{          Find The Best Defense -  introduction         }
^-|fp||cp||at|^*BPlan Your Defense^*N
After the opening lead is made, you will also see the dummy. In addition to deciding what card you should play, you should be thinking about planning your defense. |
PG| ***** 1 ***** |


AT|

^*BNext You Need to Count the HCP^*N
Without counting, even if your instincts are good, it is impossible to defend well. What should you be trying to count? High card points is one thing. Begin by counting yours and adding what the dummy has. You hope to zero in on the number of points declarer has and therefore know what partner is likely to have.|
PG| ***** 2 ***** |


AT|

^*BCount Distribution^*N
Very often the bidding will give nice clues as to what declarer's distribution is. |
PG| ***** 3 ***** |


AT|

^*BStudy the Opening Lead^*N
When partner makes the opening lead, think about what you know about his hand from the lead. Also try to memorize the opening lead.|
PG| ***** 4 ***** |


AT|

^*BPick the Suit Where You May Have a Chance^*N
When possible try to focus on which suits your side has a chance to win tricks in. |
PG| ***** 5 ***** |


AT|



