^b@2^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|I hope you would not lead a 4th round of diamonds giving declarer a ruff/sluff. There is no possible reason for you to do that. The question is: which black suit should you lead? Might partner have the @CA? Sure. You have ten HCP and dummy has 12. That leaves 18 HCP for the other 2 players. South only needs 12 HCP to open or even 11 HCP with an unbalanced hand. So partner could have an ace. But there is no advantage in leading clubs. The @CA won't go away. |
